'd like to see collected all the mentions of the suffix &quot;Thex&quot;, animal, vegetable, metal, etc..<br>
<br>
Here's what I have, and is all confirmed by my physical eye:<br>
<br>
Cristanos Thex (Queen of the Teir`Dal, correctly spelled here, not as when you kill Kizdean Gix, who names her &quot;Christanosthex&quot;)<br>
<br>
Thex Dagger (speak goofy words to Kizdean Giz, talk to a skele, collect the parts, and make neato weapons)<br>
<br>
Thex Mallet (see above, it's a container used to make the Thex Dagger)<br>
<br>
Naythox Thex (His Majesty, Ruler of Neriak and the Teir`Dal, or so SOME say.. if you hail various guards in Neriak, you'll hear a blasphemous litany. Kill certain baddies, and they'll tell you his name is Aythox Thex. I tell you, Teir`Dals are misrepresented EVERYWHERE.)<br>
<br>
King Thex Ka IV (Fourth in a dynasty of goblin kings in Permafrost, how the heck did a goblin get a royal name? How the heck did 4 of them survive? This Thex is completely expendable, I kill him on sight.)<br>
<br>
Princess Lenya Thex (In Felwithe, I hear she's fishy, but cannot confirm, because I don't want to.)<br>
<br>
King Tearis Thex (High Elf King of Felwithe, I might even say King of Faydwer if I were drunk enough. An arrogant hothead, he sliced Danak's head off before the Iksar could confess. Go figure, High Elves aren't so great at espionage either.. Now, I haven't actually &quot;met&quot; this king, but I have heard him shout across the Faydark.)<br>
<br>
So, who care's about &quot;Thex&quot;? I have a theory that &quot;thex&quot; simply is a surname that means &quot;royal&quot; or &quot;king&quot;. Perhaps this is a carry-over from the Combine Empire? Else, how do we explain a butt-bearing Goblin in this mix? Thex must lead to something grand..<br>
<br>
Any thoughts?<br>
<br>
